Your project uses **MSTest 3.8.0** on **net8.0**. The latest is **MSTest 4.1.0**. Your target framework is fine (net8.0 is supported). Here's what affects your code and what else to watch for:

---

### 🔴 Breaking change in YOUR code: `[ExpectedException]` removed

Both usages (lines 9 and 16) will fail to compile. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => Process());
}
```

---

### 📋 Other v4 breaking changes (not in your current code, but worth knowing)

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException<T>()` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` |
| `Assert.AreEqual` with format string + params removed | Use string interpolation: `$"msg {val}"` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` with no argument |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Change to `.ContainsKey()` |
| `[Timeout(TestTimeout.Infinite)]` | Use `[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` | Use `[TestMethod(DisplayName = "name")]` |
| net5.0/net6.0/net7.0 dropped | Use net8.0+ |

### ⚠️ Behavioral changes (no build errors, but runtime differences)

- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true` — discovery warnings become failures
- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- **`TestContext.TestName`** throws if accessed in `[ClassInitialize]`

---

